            <h1 class="page-header" style="margin-top: 0px;color: darkred;">Badges</h1>
            <h3 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 20px;">Easily highlight new or unread items by adding a span class="badge"
                to links, Bootstrap navs, and more.</h3>
            <div class="border" style="border: 2px solid #f5f5f5;padding-left: 30px; padding-bottom: 30px;" >
                <h4 style="color: darkgray;padding-bottom: 50px; ">Example</h4>
                <a href="#">Inbox <span class="badge">42</span></a>

                <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button">
                    Messages <span class="badge">4</span>
                </button>
            </div>
            <h4 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 20px;">Self collapsing</h4>
            <h5 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 40px;">When there are no new or unread items, badges will simply collapse
                (via CSS's :empty selector) provided no content exists within.</h5>
            <h4 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 20px;">Cross-browser compatibility</h4>
            <h5 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 40px;">Badges won't self collapse in Internet Explorer
                8 because it lacks support for the :empty selector.</h5>
            <h4 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 20px;">Adapts to active nav states</h4>
            <h5 style="color: darkred;padding-bottom: 20px;">Built-in styles are included for
                placing badges in active states in pill navigations.</h5>
            <div class="border" style="border: 2px solid #f5f5f5;padding-left: 30px; padding-bottom: 30px;" >
